description:
&lt;p&gt;An opportunity has arisen for a Band 6 Clinical Research Nurse post within the GI &amp; Lymphoma Research Unit, Chelsea. The post holder will be working with the GI &amp; Lymphoma Clinical Research Team at The Royal Marsden NHS Foundation Trust in Chelsea. &lt;br /&gt;The successful applicant ideally should have experience in managing specific clinical trials or relevant experience in managing a patient caseload. They will be working within a team that manages a portfolio of studies both sponsored, commercial and non-commercial studies. They will be responsible for ensuring their allocated clinical trials are set up and managed in accordance with regulatory, sponsor and Clinical Research and Development Office requirements. The successful candidate will be required to work as a self directed practitioner and have strong team working relationships.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt; The post holder will require to be flexible as they may neeed to work in Sutton to cover the services as and when required.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interviews will be held on 18th &lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;November 2020&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Alexandra Diaz, Lead Research Nurse, Alexandra.Diaz@rmh.nhs.uk, 0207 352 8171 Ext 4847&lt;/p&gt;
